<br>
Am I the only one to find it unfair that mages are the only casters (along with clerics but they have unlimited healing items like donal's sleeves) without any form of USEFUL mana regeneration. PLEASE oh PLEASE dont talk to me about modulation rods. Those are in no way used to effectively gain mana back. They are a useless 1 charge item that costs more mana to summon than it gives back, even when specialised in Conjuration, and is mostly used to very little results in raids and to kill unsuspecting newbies.<br>
<br>
Would it be so unbalancing to give us mages SOME sort of efficient mana regen ability? Hell, they could even make it so that we suck it away from a source that could be dangerous to all if abused, like our pet's health bar. I've always felt it would be nice, being the so-called master of the elements and so forth, to be able to sap our pet's life energy and convert it (with a very bad ratio but HEY it would be SOMETHING) to mana for the master of the pet. Say 5hp from the pet for 1 mana. Thats a 5 to 1 ratio. Make it a even higher ratio if you want. Call it Elemental Bond or somesuch. Or add a breeze effect to Shield of the Magi or why not Phantom Armore which already costs 1.2pp to cast? How would that be unbalancing? Usually once a mage is OOM thats it for the fight. He has to put his life into the hands of the people around him and his pet. Necros have lichform, wizards have harvest and manasink, shamen have cannibalize, enchanters have clarity I and II, even druid now have a form of mana regen at 54.<br>
<br>
On another note, I think that other than more useful summons, Magicians should be given a lot more control over the elements, such as elemental charm/fear. How many mobs in EQ are actually elementals? Would that be so unbalancing?<br>
<br>
I'd like to have everyone's opinion on this. And please stay constructive. I play a level 55 mage and this affects me as much as the next mage, and I only want whats best for our class. This isn't a class envy post per say, its just a serious and real problem I see with our class.<br>
<br>
Please keep the &quot;we have mod rods&quot; and &quot;mages can solo all their lives if they want&quot; arguments to yourselves, because I KNOW of them already. Necros can solo all of their lives if they wish too, yet they have mana regen.<br>
<br>
P.S.: I'd post my suggestions myself in the official mage talk thread but I dont trust that kind of website as far as I can throw them, and I cant throw them. So if anyone wants to add these suggestions to the discussion on my or your behalf, be my guest.<br>
