<br>
I most certainly can agree.. mages need some mana regen.<br>
<br>
The thing is this will never happen.<br>
<br>
As for Mages damage output, I am level 58, my experiences:<br>
<br>
Zone:  Skyfire<br>
MOBs:  Level 40-51<br>
Group Members:<br>
Mage level 58<br>
Monk level 56<br>
Monk level 51<br>
Wizard level 57<br>
Cleric level 58<br>
Druid level 51<br>
<br>
I summoned and tested pets for 20 minutes until I got a level 49 player level Earth Elemental (57th level spell) that hit for 60 max.<br>
<br>
The pet outdamaged the level 51 Monk by around 30 percent, and the level 56 Monk by around 10 percent.<br>
<br>
I added the damage up and then asked the Wizard for her damage total (unresisted).  On average after many battles the Wizard was beating the mage pet (note mage not included) for 200 or so hit points of damae.  Thats it.<br>
True this was against MOBs that have heavy MR.<br>
<br>
The Druid and Cleric were busy healing and buffing.<br>
<br>
For up to 70% burn I could output around 7k in damage myself in under a minute (not including pet).<br>
<br>
The problem is not against these MOBs (for damage), its against level 55+ MOBs.  In those encounters only Melee, Cleric, and Chanters are required.<br>
<br>
Mages are hard to play because if your pet goes your toast.  We have had to deal with this relaity for our entire career.  Why should we also have to deal with not being group desired much post 50 and not being able to contribute against many post 55 MOBs?  I think Necros and wizards have similar complaints here.  Yeah a root spell or a mana regen spell would be great but the fact is we lived without them for our entire career.  We deal damage, why not just insure we can do more of the same on post 55 MOBs?<br>
<br>
Most of us started this class to deal damage.  Seeing Wizards and Druids kite 4+ MOBs and jump from level 49 to 54 in half the time it takes us is very discoraging.  But when the circumstances are right in groups we outdamage them and all other classes on MOBs up to maybe level 52+.<br>
<br>
At the top end though we deal no great damage and are not a consideration.  We can join:  Rangers, Wizards, Necros and Shaman as classes lest likely to be asked to come on a raid against MOBs of Level 52+ in level at more then 20k or so HPs.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
What I think will help:<br>
<br>
In my opinion the level 49 fire pet needs to have a post 55th level sibling that hits for 60, has the same or almost the same HPs as the air pet and casts a upgraded fire based dd.  This pet would be the most damage dealing pet we have and would balance our pet choices against level 55+ MOBS.<br>
<br>
In my opinion mages and wizards need unresisted damage spells post 50.  Wizards get them at 60, thats way to late in the game.  These spells should be scaled where the mage version does 1/2 the damage of the Wizard version.  The spells should not cost anything more then a perl to cast and should not be MOB specific.<br>
<br>
As for mana regen its somthing that would be great but I think we can live wihtout it if the above are done to somme degree.<br>
<br>
My suspicion is that nothing will be done to help mages and that we could very well find ourselves nerfed again.  My guess is we will loose our DOTs and get magic based spells in return that are slightly faster casting then even Char is but the damage will be scaled back even further.  I also suspect that the Monster Summoning II and III pet spells will soon be changed not to cast at all (even procing stopped).<br>
<br>
<br>
Rthen Majere<br>
Level 58 Conjurer<br>
